docs.text: Let's Encrypt Standalone on Centos 7 sudo yum --enablerepo=extras install epel-release sudo yum install certbot certbot --version sudo certbot certonly --standalone --preferred-challenges http -d example.com Auto-Renewal sudo systemctl enable --now certbot-renew.timer sudo systemctl status certbot-renew.timer Renew Hook sudo vi /etc/letsencrypt/renewal/example.com.conf renew_hook = systemctl reload rabbitmq - This goes on the last line. sudo certbot renew --dry-run
